<P>
<b>WHO RECEIVES PUBLIC ASSISTANCE?</b><p>
Of foreign born 6.6%, of native born 4.9%
<p><b>Excluding refugee and elderly subgroups:</b><ul>
<p><li>
non-refugee, working age immigrants 5.1%
<p><li>working-age native born 5.3%
</ul><p>Source: <I>Current Population Survey,</I> March 1994
<p><b>1990 Census, working age population, ages 15-64, on welfare:</b><ul>
<p><li>2.0% of all new (1980-90) non-refugee immigrants
<p><li>3.2% of all non-refugee immigrants admitted before 1980
<p><li>3.7% of the native born population
<p><li>13.4% of refugees admitted 1980-90
</ul><p><b>Welfare recipients age 15 and over (1990 Census)</b><ul>
<p><li>2.8% of all new (1980-90) non-refugee immigrants
<p><li>4.2% of the native born population
<p><li>4.9% of all non-refugee immigrants admitted before 1980
<p><li>15.6% of all refugees admitted 1980-90 
</ul><p><b>Elderly over age 65 on Welfare (1990 Census)</b><ul>
<p><li>6.9% of the native born population
<p><li>11.1% of all non-refugee immigrants admitted before 1980
<p><li>25.7% of all new (1980-90) non-refugee immigrants
<p><li>49.6% of all refugees admitted 1980-90 
</ul><p>Source: <I>Urban Institute</I>

